    "body": "I don't think that is the problem here.\r\n\r\nThe reason why execution fails immediately is that provided gas is too high in this context. There is a part of the code that checks for this https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/blob/da00e949c4d8affae2589e7ab79137b7016d6255/cmd/rpcdaemon/commands/eth_call.go#L146 this part will compute correct available gas when transaction type is 0, but it doesn't work with London gas fields.\r\n\r\nI think that go-ethereum accounted for this case, see https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/e185a8c8181a2153150e0da8b7dfd3d7a95f8b22/internal/ethapi/api.go#L1012",
